# Trivy misconfiguration suppressions (infra/)
#
# Inline #trivy:ignore: comments do not work when a resource is evaluated
# through a module call (trivy issue 6941), which is the case for every finding
# here. This file is the reliable mechanism. Each ID below is a conscious,
# documented decision, not an oversight.

# ─── TRIVY IGNORE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# AWS-0132: S3 buckets use AES256 (SSE-S3), not a customer-managed KMS key.
# Deliberate for a portfolio with no sensitive data; SSE-KMS/CMK is documented
# as the PII-path upgrade in docs/adrs/0004.
AVD-AWS-0132

# AWS-0104: EMR security groups allow unrestricted egress. EMR needs outbound to
# S3, ECR, the EMR Steps API and bootstrap package mirrors; AWS service ranges
# are not statically pinnable. Documented in docs/ARCHITECTURE.md.
AVD-AWS-0104

# AWS-0136: SNS cost-alerts topic is encrypted with the AWS-managed key
# (alias/aws/sns). A customer-managed CMK is disproportionate for non-sensitive
# cost notifications; CMK is the upgrade path if alerts ever carry sensitive data.
AVD-AWS-0136
